-It's a story that still gets told.

01:00:48.967 --> 01:00:52.228
[Jacob] So we're going through
older neighborhoods in Fayetteville

01:00:52.295 --> 01:00:53.903
that have been here for decades.

01:00:53.970 --> 01:00:57.898
So it's kind of not the lavish
new builds that you see…

01:00:57.965 --> 01:01:00.435
-This house is my best friend's.
…more character.

01:01:00.502 --> 01:01:03.546
-So this is your middle class?
-This is just everyday…

01:01:03.613 --> 01:01:05.860
Yeah, and we got an elementary school.

01:01:05.927 --> 01:01:09.445
-Right. 'Cause people are gonna see this
and think everyone is super wealthy.

01:01:09.512 --> 01:01:11.943
-No. That's not the case.
-That's never the case.

01:01:12.010 --> 01:01:15.634
The theme of this video is showing
the prosperous side of Arkansas.

01:01:15.701 --> 01:01:17.663
It doesn't show everything.
Keep that in mind.

01:01:17.730 --> 01:01:20.790
They'll be like, "I grew up in Fayetteville
and it's not all like that."

01:01:20.857 --> 01:01:22.582
It's definitely not all like this.

01:01:22.649 --> 01:01:27.168
And things have changed so fast that
it's hard for the older locals to keep up.

01:01:27.696 --> 01:01:28.579
-I bet.

01:01:28.646 --> 01:01:31.903
-People who have been here
their whole lives change the ways.

01:01:31.970 --> 01:01:35.286
But, like, students live in these.
This is student housing.

01:01:35.353 --> 01:01:38.063
-What's your guys' rent like
in a place like that?

01:01:38.130 --> 01:01:40.362
-So it's been going up the past few years.

01:01:40.429 --> 01:01:45.381
But I'd say average is
$800 or $900 a month up to…

01:01:45.448 --> 01:01:47.523
-For a one bedroom?
-For each kid.

01:01:47.590 --> 01:01:50.750
-Oh, okay. 
-And it's kind of individualized.

01:01:51.520 --> 01:01:54.395
So in a house,
you have four bedrooms, it's gonna be $800?

01:01:54.462 --> 01:01:56.882
We each pay $800 or $900.

01:01:56.949 --> 01:01:58.833
Some of the nicer ones are $1,200.

01:01:58.900 --> 01:02:02.519
It is known that there's
a housing and parking shortage here.

01:02:02.586 --> 01:02:06.593
-And that's a part of the reason
why prices have gone up so much

01:02:06.660 --> 01:02:08.566
so quickly in recent years.

01:02:08.633 --> 01:02:10.906
I also pay like $800 a month

01:02:10.973 --> 01:02:14.363
for my bedroom in my apartment
which is kind of ridiculous.

01:02:14.430 --> 01:02:17.227
-These are all brand new builds.
-That's wild.

01:02:17.294 --> 01:02:18.823
Targeted towards students.

01:02:22.230 --> 01:02:24.760
[Peter] Who do we have in the back, Jacob?

01:02:24.827 --> 01:02:28.304
So not only do we have Zach,
we have my lovely lady, Jocelyn.

01:02:28.371 --> 01:02:30.446
-Jocelyn's in the mix.
-She's joining us.

01:02:30.513 --> 01:02:31.851
Nice to see you guys.

01:02:31.918 --> 01:02:35.453
-And you guys were saying off camera,
homework, how much a week?

01:02:35.520 --> 01:02:39.299
I spend a few hours a week on homework.

01:02:39.366 --> 01:02:41.988
Yeah, I'd agree.
I usually do all my stuff on Sunday.

01:02:42.055 --> 01:02:44.228
If not, maybe one hour a day.

01:02:45.038 --> 01:02:46.195
-Are you serious?
-Yeah.

01:02:46.262 --> 01:02:48.698
That's all you guys do
in university these days?

01:02:48.765 --> 01:02:51.643
-Yeah. You go to class.
-That's all you have to do.

01:02:51.710 --> 01:02:52.669
That's basically…

01:02:52.736 --> 01:02:55.883
-Okay. So you're using the LLMs,
that sort of stuff?

01:02:55.950 --> 01:02:59.727
-It's just common knowledge at this point?
-We don't just copy and paste it.

01:02:59.794 --> 01:03:01.905
Well, I'll even ask it everyday questions.

01:03:01.972 --> 01:03:04.985
It's not always for school.
It just knows me at this point.

01:03:05.052 --> 01:03:07.602
I feel like I talk to it
more than Jacob sometimes.

01:03:07.669 --> 01:03:09.970
-No, that's so sad. Talk to Jacob more.

01:03:10.037 --> 01:03:10.920
-Yeah, yeah.

01:03:11.513 --> 01:03:13.573
-But it's true.
We use it for a lot of stuff.

01:03:13.640 --> 01:03:16.448
That's so wild.
So you guys don't have to do,

01:03:16.515 --> 01:03:20.406
like your term papers
are not super painful now.

01:03:20.950 --> 01:03:22.965
I wouldn't say I use it for everything.

01:03:23.032 --> 01:03:25.105
It really just depends on the assignment.

01:03:25.172 --> 01:03:26.969
-Okay.
-Or the word count sometimes.

01:03:27.036 --> 01:03:30.283
I'm like, give me filler words
for so-and-so.

01:03:30.350 --> 01:03:31.329
But main ideas.

01:03:31.396 --> 01:03:33.623
-And then grammar, spelling,
you don't have to know that anymore.

01:03:33.690 --> 01:03:34.943
-You just run it through.
-Yeah.

01:03:35.010 --> 01:03:38.936
That being said though, I mean, you got
to come on test day knowing your stuff.

01:03:39.003 --> 01:03:40.764
-Like I use…
-That's the difference.

01:03:40.831 --> 01:03:42.982
…GPT's study and quiz tools
to help me study.

01:03:43.049 --> 01:03:46.473
Yeah. They'll make you flashcards,
a whole Quizlet, everything.

01:03:46.540 --> 01:03:48.346
Especially, I take math classes.

01:03:48.413 --> 01:03:50.795
Like you can't GPT your way through

01:03:50.862 --> 01:03:53.944
a math or other like
engineering and STEM courses.

01:03:54.011 --> 01:03:58.809
But it's like a great study tool and it
helps you work efficiently, I would say.

01:03:59.731 --> 01:04:03.167
I can just put my lecture notes in
and be like, give me a study guide for this

01:04:03.234 --> 01:04:06.297
and put the points that the module
will give me for the study guide.

01:04:06.364 --> 01:04:10.202
If I put that in there, it'll give me
exactly what I need for the test.

01:04:10.269 --> 01:04:12.571
-Makes studying a lot quicker.
-Yeah.

01:04:12.638 --> 01:04:16.769
And I will add on
from the data science department,

01:04:17.310 --> 01:04:19.421
like working in the tech field,

01:04:19.488 --> 01:04:23.348
our department from last year
to this year, almost like flipped.

01:04:23.415 --> 01:04:25.837
It was very anti AI, like don't use AI.

01:04:25.904 --> 01:04:27.757
And now they want you to use it.

01:04:27.824 --> 01:04:31.163
Yeah. You're like required to use it
in a lot of courses now.

01:04:31.230 --> 01:04:33.178
-Because it's changed a lot.

01:04:33.245 --> 01:04:37.363
And they think you're going to be behind
if you don't know how to use it.

01:04:39.391 --> 01:04:40.920
[Jacob] Wright's Barbecue.

01:04:42.060 --> 01:04:44.060
